message.entry: Type: ''{0}'' is not recognized. Refer to the datastore documentation for supported values of Type.
Do not specify Type multiple times.
Type must be a nonempty character vector. Refer to the datastore documentation for supported values of Type.
Cannot determine the datastore type for the specified location.\n\nSpecify the 'Type' name-value pair argument to indicate the type of datastore to create.
Specify 'FileExtensions' along with 'Type' Name-Value pair argument.
Undefined function ''{0}'' for input arguments of type ''{1}''.
'DatastoreType' Name-Value pair is discouraged.\n\nSpecify only 'Type' Name-Value pair instead.
'Type' or 'DatastoreType' cannot be a property while using the datastore function.\n\nRemove 'Type' or 'DatastoreType' from your class or directly construct using ''{0}(LOCATION)''.
FileExtensions must begin with ''.'' or be empty quotes ''''.
